Package musichub.util

Interface AudioToXML

All Known Implementing Classes:
Album, AudioBook, AudioElement, Playlist, Song
public interface AudioToXML
Represents an object that can be loaded from and to XML via the AudioXML class.
Class implementing this interface should always have a constructor with 0 arguments.

  • Method Details

    • load

      void load​(java.util.Map<java.lang.String,​java.util.List<java.lang.String>> attributes)
      Given a list of attributes as parameter, stores this attributes in an instance of the class (previously created).
      If the attribute corresponding to a name is only a single value (as opposed to a list), it will appear in the map as a list containing only one element
      Parameters:
      attributes - a map of all the attributes, mapped by name

    • save

      java.util.Map<java.lang.String,​java.util.List<java.lang.String>> save()
      Puts all the attributes of the class to be saved into an XML file into a map.
      The key should be the name of the attribute.
      The value should be a list of values, or a list of one value if the attribute is not a list itself.
      Returns:
      the Map created

    • toList

      static java.util.List<java.lang.String> toList​(java.lang.String attribute)
      Transforms a String into a List<String> containing only this element.
      Parameters:
      attribute - the element to put in the list
      Returns:
      a list containing only one element
